# Tayseer ERP — File Organization Rules

NEVER create new files directly in the project root. Every file has a designated location.

## Directory Map

| File type | Correct location | Example |
|-----------|-----------------|---------|
| Python check/health scripts | `scripts/check/` | `_check_db.py` |
| Python debug scripts | `scripts/debug/` | `_debug_route.py` |
| Python deploy/upload scripts | `scripts/deploy/` | `_deploy_changes.py` |
| Python fix/patch scripts | `scripts/fix/` | `_fix_ssl.py` |
| Python server mgmt scripts | `scripts/server/` | `_restart_apache.py` |
| Python verify scripts | `scripts/verify/` | `_verify_server.py` |
| Python misc utilities | `scripts/misc/` | `_cleanup.py` |
| SQL files & views | `database/sql/` | `phase1_views.sql` |
| DB seed/test data | `database/seeds/` | `_seed_data.php` |
| Migration helper scripts | `database/migrations/` | `setup_remote.sh` |
| Docker/container files | `deploy/docker-legacy/` | `Dockerfile` |
| SSH/SFTP tools | `deploy/sshfs/` | `fix_sftp.sh` |
| Feature specs & design docs | `docs/specs/` | `FEATURE_SPEC.md` |
| System reports & analysis | `docs/reports/` | `SYSTEM_REPORT.md` |
| Diagnostic/log outputs | `docs/diagnostics/` | `error_log.txt` |
| Reference PDFs/attachments | `docs/attachments/` | `document.pdf` |
| Setup/how-to guides | `docs/` | `setup-guide.md` |

## Root-level files (ONLY these are allowed)

These are the ONLY files that belong in the project root:

- `.gitignore`, `.htaccess` — Git & Apache config
- `composer.json` — PHP dependencies
- `phpstan.neon` — Static analysis config
- `requirements.php` — Yii2 requirements checker
- `init`, `init.bat`, `yii.bat` — Yii2 entry scripts
- `README.md`, `LICENSE.md` — Project docs

## Naming conventions for scripts

- Prefix with `_` for utility scripts: `_check_db.py`, `_fix_ssl.py`
- Use snake_case for all script filenames
- Group related scripts by their action verb: check, debug, deploy, fix, verify

## When creating ANY new file

1. Determine file type from the table above
2. Place it in the correct directory — NEVER in root
3. If unsure, ask the user before creating in root
